<br>
Level 43 Chanter, light blue pet, DL.... used to be that combination (well, it would have been a green pet, for sure) would mean, &quot;Donating for Rez!&quot; soon afterwards. However, it worked like a charm. As soon as the pet started getting too low, zap, mezzed mob, &quot;Sorry, I cannot attack a mesmerized target&quot; (or whatever he said.) <br>
<br>
At that point, you have multiple options. First, you can med a while. Your pet regens pretty fast so this gives him a chance to heal up a bit. Reapply the rampage to yourself and your pet (rune3 may only cost 7gp per, but they add up) and nuke the mob to wake him up.<br>
<br>
I think on it's own, the pet did about half the damage. That isn't a problem, though, because sometime back they changed it so that as long as you do ANY damage, you get all of the exp.<br>
<br>
Now for yourself you'll probably want all of your usual buffs, but you might consider rampage over rune. You're gonna take a lot of hits. I'd also suggest fire ele illusion for the DS. Oh, and since you're using rampage, augmentation would be a good idea as well.<br>
<br>
For your pet, shield, aug, feedback, rampage and I think thats about it. I believe you'll want to hand him a second weapon as well.<br>
<br>
Don't even mem your DoT. Don't even think about it. Just keep tash, slow, aug, rampage, root, and I like gate along with a couple DD's, although you might want one DD and your longest stun.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I spent the last 6 months or so playing my monk, just because I'd rather solo than group. I just started playing my chanter again, and this just may keep me back for a while. <br>
<br>
